Skater Taxonomy - Jim Greco

The graphs arent necessarily the best visual representation of the underlying data, so once we hone in on what we want to show, I can export PNGs of the charts so you can trace them in Illustrator/whatever the process for a Jenkem aesthetic is. Also if theres something you want me to investigate, let me know! Ill do it so as long as its possible with the dataset I created.

Stuff I Think We Should Highlight

  • top tricks are mostly what we expect (bs 360, switch fs flip variations, etc.)
  • top tricks by video part
  • Greco loves to skate sloped stuff, and does so a lot (E.g. banks, curbcuts, natural quarterpipes). He did a lot at the beginning of his career, stopped in the middle, and did a lot at the end of his career.
  • Decline of stair + handrail skating over time (Hammers USA was not a lot of hammers).
  • Grecos best (traditional) video part in terms of trick diversity + unique trick count: The Deathwish Video. (Sober Greco = more productive narrative?).
  • baker2g is his worst video part. It used by FAR the most repeated angles, the most slow-motion, as well as the lowest number of tricks (both total and unique). I didnt track locations unfortunately, but Im pretty sure that part is like 90% wilshire.

Graphs For Stuff I Said We Should Highlight

  • top tricks are mostly what we expect (bs 360, switch fs flip variations, etc.)

Important - Given that Greco did a trick down stairs, theres a 33% chance it was a switch fs flips or nollie bs flips! (not shown in graph, but definitely worth a mention). I.e., 1/3 of Grecos tricks down stairs were switch fs flip variations.

  • top tricks by video part

  • Greco loves to skate sloped stuff, and does so a lot (E.g. banks, curbcuts, natural quarterpipes). He did a lot at the beginning of his career, stopped in the middle, and did a lot at the end of his career.

  • Decline of stair + handrail skating over time (Hammers USA was not a lot of hammers).

  • baker2g is his worst video part. It used by FAR the most repeated angles, the most slow-motion, as well as had the lowest number of tricks (both total and unique). I didnt track locations unfortunately, but Im pretty sure that part is like 90% wilshire, so lacks spot diversity as well.

Sober Greco Is Killing It - Grecos best (traditional) video part in terms of trick diversity + unique trick count: The Deathwish Video.

Summary Stats (just raw numbers)

Total number of clips (including multiple angles): 464.

Total number of tricks across all videos (not counting double-angles): 389.

Number of unique tricks (i.e.dont count double-angles) where Greco skates a car: 10.

Total number of manual tricks: 7.

Total number of switch clips: 79.

Number of tricks with more than one angle: 69.

Number of flatground tricks: 51.

Number of lines: 40.

Number of tricks in longest line: 4.

Number of tricks involving slopes (i.e.curbcuts, banks, natural quarterpipes, etc.): 138.

Number of slow-mo clips: 77.
